==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hemicycle
<hw>Hem"i*cy`cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>hemicyclus</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ + <grk>ky`klos</grk>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A half circle; a semicircle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 685 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A semicircular place, as a semicircular arena, or
room, or part of a room.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The collections will be displayed in the <qex>hemicycle</qex> of
the central pavilion.</q> <rj><qau>London Academy.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hemidactyl</ent>⟦br⟧
